latestPosts.caption:
Thankgod for these awkward teen years, they’ve honestly given me the confidence to take on anything in the world.

Its hard when youre going through it.
I was bullied, people looked at me w a disappointing look on their face , my parents expressed their concern several times, and I’ve cried innumerable hours about how I looked, I DID FEEL SHIT but looking back I dont regret anything! 
I was a happy healthy human being, and i went through alot at a time to lose all the weight, obsessively, I might add.
developed a mild eating disorder and my body dysmorphia reached a concerning level. 
NOTHING MADE ME HAPPY

10 years later, having gone through the entire body image selling market and its after effects i can tell you one thing :

A. Its more of a sham than they let on.
B. You could think you look like shit and still actually look like a million dollars but if you FEEL like shit ( atleast about your body ) no amount of dressing up or makeup or ‘changes’ in your body will make you feel better!

Unfortunately, Acceptance is the only key! Your body is the only ONE thing thats actually yours in this life, why do you have to fight with it? Why cant we JUST love it? The same love we give away like confetti? Your body deserves it. YOU deserve it.

#bodypositivity #skincare #bodydysmorphia

Help us all!!

Taking care of yourself is a process, you may not see the results you aim for, but as long as you’re a little bit better than yesterday, You’ll get there!

Pointers to save!
1. Only do things that you can be consistent with, idealism doesnt show results.

2. Over way too many years i have realised B&G’s avocado oil has ALWAYS been very nourishing to my hair, and is easily available.
I try to oil at least once a week.

A lot of people have discouraged me but i feel it always helps my hair, though its said oil shouldnt go on the scalp but ive realised it helps my hair so i do it anyway

3. Shampoo your hair when its dirty, irrespective of whether its once twice or thrice a week.

4. I cannot stress enough on using a hair conditioner post shampoo, honestly game changer! But only on the tips.

5. Protective hairstyles like a braid REALLY GOES A LONG WAY. Especially before sleeping.

6. Cold water - you can fight it as long as you want, I did too, but if you want better hair. COLD WATWR RINSE IS A MUST!

7. Last for this post, what you dry your hair with post shower is SO IMPORTANT! Use a soft towel, i found mine in miniso. And use a heat protective serum REGARDLESS!

De- influencing because you dont need everything that goes viral.
Listening to your skin is the most important step in skincare.
Be wise with your money and picky with your akincare

Always works for me!
I hope it works for you too!

Disclaimer : this is from personal experience hence i thought i should share.
When you exfoliate, make sure you use ceramides in your moisturiser 
Spf is very important to prevent and reduce tan.
Retinol isnt for everyone, make sure to patch test and ALWAYS moisturiser before and after retinol!

Other than that, always patch test. ALWAYS listen to your skin.
Xoxo
